name: EA-003-Aristóteles
description:
Aristotle (384 - 322 BC) was a Greek philosopher during the classical period in ancient Greece, founder of the Peripatetic school and the Lyceum, as well as being a pupil of Plato and a teacher of Alexander the Great.

Digital Watercolor Vector Illustration made in Adobe Photoshop, 1200x1200px, 200dpi, JPEG
